# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env` in both `root` and `client` directories.

## Server (.env in root/server)

```
# MongoDB
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/edumart

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_here

# Email Configuration (Nodemailer)
EMAIL_USER=your_email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your_app_password

# Firebase Admin
FIREBASE_ADMIN_SDK_PATH=./path-to-serviceAccountKey.json

# Server Port
PORT=5000

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=production
```

## Client (.env in client)

```
# API Configuration
REACT_APP_API_URL=https://your-backend-url.com

# Firebase Web Config
REACT_APP_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSyD...
REACT_APP_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
REACT_APP_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
REACT_APP_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.appspot.com
REACT_APP_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=123456789
REACT_APP_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:123456789:web:abc...
```

## How to Get These Values

### MongoDB Atlas
1. Go to [mongodb.com/cloud/atlas](https://mongodb.com/cloud/atlas)
2. Create a cluster (free tier available)
3. Get connection string from "Connect" button

### Firebase
1. Go to [firebase.google.com](https://firebase.google.com)
2. Create a new project
3. Go to Project Settings â†’ Your apps
4. Copy the config values

### JWT Secret
Generate a random string:
```bash
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

### Email Configuration
- Use Gmail with App Password (2FA enabled)
- Don't use your regular Gmail password

